  "lastMessage": "## Wave 1A Audit Complete\n\n**File:** `.planning/debug/audit-2026-06-04/wave-1a-tool-surface-and-sessions.md`\n**Line count:** 695 lines (74,280 bytes) — within the 500–800 target band\n**Total issues found:** 15 (5 CRITICAL, 6 HIGH, 4 MEDIUM)\n**Confidence:** HIGH\n\n### Top 5 Critical Issues\n\n1. **`src/tools/hivemind/run-background-command.ts:1` registered as delegation tool** — File lives in `tools/hivemind/` but is wired up by `registerDelegationTools` at `src/plugin.ts:144`. Misleads maintainers searching `tools/delegation/`.\n2. **`src/features/governance-engine/create-governance-session.ts:80` outside `src/tools/`** — Breaks the \"27 tools in `src/tools/`\" invariant from AGENTS.md. Registered at `src/plugin.ts:163`.\n3. **`src/plugin.ts:173` docstring drift** — Claims \"Record of 8 hivemind tools\" but `src/plugin.ts:175-187` registers **9** entries (off by one, correlates with late addition of `session-delegation-query`).\n4. **Dual-source delegation readers return different shapes** — `src/tools/delegation/readers/session-tracker-reader.ts:15-88` vs `legacy-reader.ts:16-58`. Same `Delegation` type, different field semantics (e.g. `agent`, `queueKey`, `nestingDepth` differ). No source discriminator in tool output.\n5. **Session-tracker and continuity both own session lifecycle** — `src/features/session-tracker/index.ts:100` (SessionTracker) writes per-session `*.md`/`*.json` files while `src/task-management/continuity/index.ts:38-51` writes the single `session-continuity.json` — two parallel stores with no transactional boundary and a documented CQRS contract (`features/session-tracker/index.ts:8-12`) that the continuity module violates.\n\nDocument covers: full 27-tool table with schema source + actions + engine integration + output envelope, 5-surface session-tracker ecosystem map with readers/writers, complete engine/lib/hook/feature topology across 21 coordination files + 14 hook files + 18,948 LOC of features + 2,540 LOC of schemas, 15 cross-track conflicts (file-path vs registration domain, dual-source persistence, schema drift, read/write authority), 15 fully-cited issues with file:line + impact + proposed remedy (no source changes performed).\n\nReady for orchestrator summary."
